  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">E-Schools Online Training</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SK">E-Schools Online Training</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="SK">Projekt E-School bol iniciovan&#xFD; v roku 2016. Odvtedy sa do&#x148; prihl&#xE1;silo 4000 vzdel&#xE1;vac&#xED;ch in&#x161;tit&#xFA;ci&#xED; v UA. Vyu&#x10D;ovac&#xED; proces v UA prebieha vo v&#xE4;&#x10D;&#x161;ine pr&#xED;padov v online re&#x17E;ime. Tr&#xE9;ning pedag&#xF3;gov k vyu&#x17E;&#xED;vaniu tejto platformy bol umocnen&#xFD; najm&#xE4; s&#xFA;&#x10D;asnou pandemickou situ&#xE1;ciou, ktor&#xE1; neumo&#x17E;&#x148;uje fyzick&#xE9; stretnutia pedag&#xF3;gov s rodi&#x10D;mi det&#xED;. V s&#xFA;&#x10D;asnej situ&#xE1;cii nie je mo&#x17E;n&#xE9; predpoveda&#x165;, kedy sa klasick&#xFD; prezen&#x10D;n&#xFD; model vzdel&#xE1;vania obnov&#xED;. Vyu&#x17E;&#xED;vanie E-School m&#xE1; potenci&#xE1;l r&#xE1;s&#x165;.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The E-School project was initiated in 2016. Since then, 4,000 educational institutions in the UA have signed up. The teaching process in UA takes place in most cases online. The training of teachers to use this platform was intensified mainly by the current pandemic situation, which does not allow physical meetings of teachers with parents of children. In the current situation, it is not possible to predict when the classical full-time model of education will be revived. The use of E-School has the potential to grow.</narrative>
  </description>
